[Section 1.3: School Leadership and Administrative Contacts]
We encourage you to refer to this list whenever you need to contact a non-teaching member of our team for the topics listed below. You can use Phidias to get in touch with any of them.

| SUBJECT | CONTACT PERSON |  |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| School satisfaction, School Policies and Individual families’ queries. | **Mariano** Executive Director |  |
| Queries related to pedagogical topics, including the educational psychologist department. | **Sheila** Head Teacher Early Years and Primary | **Lindsay** Head Teacher Secondary |
| Inquiries about administration, school operations and the Enrichment Program. | **Sandra** Head of School Operations and Enrichment Program |  |
| Payments | **María Luisa** Administration |  |
| Tutor appointments, medication administration, absences, diet requirements, bus service, Imagine Shop, changes to the arrival/dismissal time, new or exceptional authorized persons to collect children, lost & found. | **María Luisa** / **Madhu** Secretaries |  |
| Admissions, bus service | **Hernan** |  |
| Medication administration Authorizations Bus changes (Google Form) Imagine Shop   \*It is important to use the established processes and avoid    sending direct messages to the administration. | **Phidias Process\*** |  |

---

[Section 2.7: Student pick-up/departure authorization]
Parents, guardians, and legal representatives who have properly completed their information in our Phidias records will be authorised to pick up the students.

If someone other than those listed will be picking up the students, or if you wish to authorise the students to leave on their own, you must complete the “Tracking” section in Phidias, as explained below:

[How to Authorise Student Pick-Up in Phidias](https://vimeo.com/1003094042/7c8aaad568)

---

[Section 23: Updating Contact and Family Information]
If your contact information or any other important records change during the school year, please update the new information in Phidias. It is important for the team to have the most current information available in case of an emergency.

[How to edit your profile on Phidias](https://vimeo.com/1002778715/473248fe55?share=copy)

On the other hand, if **your family situation** changes at home due to separation or divorce, we ask that you inform your guide as soon as possible so they can monitor any changes affecting your child.
········································

Answer:
To authorise a new person to collect your child from school, you must complete the “Tracking” section in Phidias [2.7]. The specific steps for this process are explained in the "How to Authorise Student Pick-Up in Phidias" resource [2.7]. Inquiries about new or exceptional authorized persons to collect children can be directed to María Luisa or Madhu, the Secretaries [1.3].

